Clayton Dubilier Close to Buying Emergency Medical, Reuter Says

-- B y   C h r i s   P e t e r s o n
-- 
2011-02-14T05:19:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-14/clayton-dubilier-close-to-buying-emergency-medical-reuter-says.html
Clayton Dubilier & Rice is close to
a deal to buy  Emergency Medical Services Corp ., Reuters
reported, citing a person familiar with the matter.  The deal, which may be announced today, values Emergency
Medical, a provider of healthcare and physician services, at
over $3 billion, the news wire said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Peterson at 
 cpeterson@bloomberg.net  